                  <handDesc><handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic"><seg type="rubrication"><foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢየሱስ፡</foreign></seg></handNote></handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#84r" facs="085">fols. 84r, </locus> multiple full stops and lines of alternating red and black dots;
                      multiple full stops are used as section dividers throughout (e.g., <locus target="#5r #6r" facs="006 007">5r, 6r</locus>).</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1"><desc><locus target="#ir" facs="001">Fol. ir</locus><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT4005Salota">Prayer against
                                                  hail</title>, in a later hand, with incipit: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በስ<supplied reason="omitted">መ፡ አብ፡</supplied> በል፡ ጸሎተ፡ በረድ፡ አብርድ፡ ኢይበርድ፡ አስተባርድ፡</foreign></desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a2"><desc><locus target="#iv" facs="002">Fol. iv</locus>Unidentified text in a later hand. Likely incomplete at the beginning.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a3"><desc type="OwnershipNote"><locus target="#84r" facs="095">Fol. 84r</locus>Mentions the name of the owner Gäbrä Mikaʾel (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>). A secondary owner, Gäbrä Täklä Haymanot (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡</foreign>) has written his name over the top of the first name.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a4"><desc><locus target="#84r" facs="085">Fol. 84r</locus>A note in a later hand asking for deliverance from ordeals of flesh and spirit for Gäbrä Täklä Haymanot (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡</foreign>).</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="a5"><desc><locus target="#84v" facs="086">Fol. 84v</locus>A note in a later hand.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e1"><desc><locus target="#27" facs="028">Fol. 27</locus> f. 27, black string sewn into fore edge as navigation system</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e2"><desc>Numbered quires: quire 1.</desc></item>
                      <item xml:id="e3"><desc>Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1r #1v #2v #3r #3v" facs="002 003 004 005">folss. 1r, 1v, 2v, 3r, 3v, </locus>, etc.);
                        and in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#4v #5r #6v #7v #9r" facs="006 007 008 010">4v, 5r, 6v, 7v, 9r, </locus>, etc.);
                        text has been removed (<locus target="#4r #8v #12v #14v #17r" facs="005 010 014 018">4r, 8v, 12v, 14v, 17r</locus>, etc.)</desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                      <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood covered with tooled leather, linen visible between the turn-ins, headband visible.</decoNote>
                      <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                        <material key="parchment"/>
                        <material key="wood"/>
                        <material key="leather"/>
                        <material key="textile"/>
                      </decoNote>
                    </binding>
